# ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê

# Kill process interactively
fkill() {
    local pids=$(ps -f -u $USER | sed 1d | fzf --multi --header='[KILL PROCESS]' | awk '{print $2}')
    if [ -n "$pids" ]; then
        echo "$pids" | xargs kill -${1:-9}
        echo "‚úì Killed process(es): $pids"
    fi
}

# Interactive directory navigation (Arch compatible)
fcd() {
    local dir
    dir=$(find ${1:-.} -path '*/\.*' -prune -o -type d -print 2> /dev/null | 
          fzf --preview 'ls -la --color=always {}' +m) && cd "$dir"
}

# Git branch management
fgb() {
    local branches branch
    branches=$(git branch -a) && 
    branch=$(echo "$branches" | fzf +s +m -e --preview 'git log --oneline --graph --color=always {}') && 
    git checkout $(echo "$branch" | sed "s/.* //" | sed "s#remotes/[^/]*/##")
}

# Service management
fsvc() {
    local service
    service=$(systemctl list-units --type=service --all | 
              fzf --header='[SERVICE MANAGER]' | awk '{print $1}')
    if [ -n "$service" ]; then
        echo "Selected: $service"
        echo "Actions: [s]tart, [t]op, [r]estart, [e]nable, [d]isable, [status]"
        read -r "action?Choose action: "
        case $action in
            s|start) sudo systemctl start "$service" ;;
            t|stop) sudo systemctl stop "$service" ;;
            r|restart) sudo systemctl restart "$service" ;;
            e|enable) sudo systemctl enable "$service" ;;
            d|disable) sudo systemctl disable "$service" ;;
            *) systemctl status "$service" ;;
        esac
    fi
}

# Port investigation (Arch compatible)
fport() {
    local port
    port=$(ss -tulpn 2>/dev/null | fzf --header='[PORT FINDER]' | awk '{print $5}' | cut -d: -f2)
    if [ -n "$port" ]; then
        echo "Port: $port"
        lsof -i :$port 2>/dev/null || echo "Permission denied or port not in use"
    fi
}

# Config file editor
fconf() {
    local file
    file=$(find ~/.config -type f \( -name "*.conf" -o -name "*.config" -o -name "*.toml" -o -name "*.yaml" -o -name "*.yml" \) 2>/dev/null | 
           fzf --preview 'bat --color=always {}') && $EDITOR "$file"
}

# Log viewer
flog() {
    local log
    log=$(find /var/log -name "*.log" 2>/dev/null | 
          fzf --preview 'tail -20 {}' --header='[LOG VIEWER]') && 
          sudo tail -f "$log"
}

# Package manager (Arch compatible)
fpac() {
    local package
    package=$(pacman -Ss . 2>/dev/null | 
              fzf --preview 'pacman -Si {1} 2>/dev/null' | cut -d' ' -f1)
    if [ -n "$package" ]; then
        echo "Selected: $package"
        read -r "confirm?Install $package? (y/N): "
        [ "$confirm" = "y" ] && sudo pacman -S "$package"
    fi
}

# Docker container manager
fdocker() {
    local container action
    container=$(docker ps -a --format "table {{.Names}}\t{{.Status}}\t{{.Image}}" | 
                fzf --header-lines=1 --header='[DOCKER MANAGER]' | awk '{print $1}')
    if [ -n "$container" ]; then
        echo "Selected: $container"
        echo "Actions: [s]tart, [t]op, [r]estart, [l]ogs, [e]xec, [rm]"
        read -r "action?Choose action: "
        case $action in
            s|start) docker start "$container" ;;
            t|stop) docker stop "$container" ;;
            r|restart) docker restart "$container" ;;
            l|logs) docker logs -f "$container" ;;
            e|exec) docker exec -it "$container" /bin/bash ;;
            rm) docker rm "$container" ;;
        esac
    fi
}

# Environment variables browser
fenv() {
    env | fzf --preview 'echo {}'
}

# Man page browser
fman() {
    local cmd=$(compgen -c | sort -u | 
                fzf --preview 'man {} 2>/dev/null | head -20' --preview-window=right:50% --header='[MAN PAGES]')
    [ -n "$cmd" ] && man "$cmd"
}

# Game ROM finder
fgame() {
    local game_file
    game_file=$(find ~/Games -type f \( -name "*.rom" -o -name "*.iso" -o -name "*.gba" -o -name "*.nds" -o -name "*.n64" -o -name "*.smc" \) 2>/dev/null | 
                fzf --preview 'echo -e "üìÅ Directory: $(dirname {})\nüìÑ File: $(basename {})\nüíæ Size: $(du -h {} | cut -f1)"' --header='[GAME SELECTOR]')
    if [ -n "$game_file" ]; then
        echo "üéÆ Selected: $(basename "$game_file")"
        cd "$(dirname "$game_file")" && ls -la --color=always
    fi
}

